I.    Introduction

A Risk Management Program has been implemented at the Benardi Frozen Foods, division of Windsor Foods (Windsor Foods) facility located at 301 West Third Street in Toluca, Illinois, for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This updated Risk Management Plan (RMP) summarizes changes that include removal of the west refrigeration system engine room and an increase of approximately 3,000 pounds to the overall site inventory of ammonia.  This RMP includes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. The RMP is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including: 

?    Introduction;

?    Windsor Foods policies to protect health, environment, and safety;

?    Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;

?    Hazard Assessment;

?    Prevention Program;

?    Five-Year Accident History;

?    Emergency Response Plan; 

?    Emergency Communications;

?    Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures;

?    Planned changes to improve safety; and

?    Management Program



II.    Windsor Foods Policies To Protect Health, Environment, and Safety

Risk management and safety are important concerns at Windsor Foods; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. Windsor Foods is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment. It is Windsor Foods' policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations.



